-- Singapore’s City Harvest Church Doubles Convention Center Stake
-- B y   L i n u s   C h u a
-- 2012-07-21T16:31:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-21/singapore-s-city-harvest-church-doubles-convention-center-stake.html
     July 22 (Bloomberg) -  Singapore ’s City Harvest Church
doubled its stake in a downtown convention center last year to
39.2 percent for an additional S$54 million, the  Straits Times 
 reported , citing Executive Pastor Aries Zulkarnain.   The church bought 19.2 percent of Suntec Singapore for the
amount, the newspaper said, citing Zulkarnain at a service at
the convention center yesterday attended by 6,000. City Harvest
first invested less than S$44 million for 20 percent of Suntec
Singapore in 2010, the newspaper said. The property is partly
owned by Suntec REIT.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Linus Chua at 
 lchua@bloomberg.net  